#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1085
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overview"
msgstr "Pregled"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1086
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some subversion operations may be used via the command line, &eg;, like a "
"standard command line client but user interaction is made through the "
"<acronym>UI</acronym>. The standard syntax is <userinput>kdesvn exec "
"<replaceable>command</replaceable> <replaceable>parameter</replaceable> "
"<replaceable>url</replaceable></userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Nekatere subverzivne operacije se lahko uporabljajo prek ukazne vrstice, "
"&eg; kot standardni odjemalec ukazne vrstice, vendar interakcija uporabnika "
"poteka prek <acronym>UI</acronym>. Standardna sintaksa je <userinput>kdesvn "
"exec <replaceable>ukaz</replaceable> <replaceable>parameter</replaceable> "
"<replaceable>url</replaceable></userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1089
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a single revision on a single &URL; is wanted it may be set as a "
"parameter of the &URL; <programlisting>svn://your-server/path-to-repository/"
"item?rev=&lt;your-rev&gt;</programlisting> This will overwrite the option "
"<option>-r &lt;rev&gt;</option>."
msgstr ""
"Če ena sama revizija na enem &URL; če želite, ga lahko nastavite kot "
"parameter &URL; <programlisting>svn://your-server/path-to-repository/item?"
"rev=&lt;your-rev&gt;</programlisting> To bo prepisalo možnost <option>-r &lt;"
"rev&gt;</option>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1093
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A revision may be given as a number or one of <option>HEAD</option> or "
"<option>BASE</option> or as date format like {YYYY-MM-DD}."
msgstr ""
"Revizija je lahko podana kot številka ali ena od <option>HEAD</option> ali "
"<option>BASE</option> ali kot oblika datuma, kot je {LLLL-MM-DD}."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1100
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If in following overview as possible parameter <option>-r "
"<replaceable>revision</replaceable></option> is given, this revision may be "
"set as <userinput><replaceable>url</replaceable>?rev=<replaceable>the-"
"revision</replaceable></userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Če je v naslednjem pregledu kot možni parameter <option>-r "
"<replaceable>revision</replaceable></option> podan, je ta revizija lahko "
"nastavljena kot <userinput><replaceable>url</replaceable>?rev=<replaceable> "
"revizija</replaceable></userinput>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1103
#, no-c-format
msgid "Subversion commands"
msgstr "Subverzivni ukazi"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1108
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command"
msgstr "Ukaz"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1109
#, no-c-format
msgid "Meaning"
msgstr "Pomen"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1110
#, no-c-format
msgid "Accepted options"
msgstr "Sprejete možnosti"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1116
#, no-c-format
msgid "commit (or ci)"
msgstr "zaveži (ali ci)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1117
#, no-c-format
msgid "commit changes of item to repository"
msgstr "potrdi spremembe postavke v repozitorij"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1121 index.docbook:1260
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>log</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>dnevnik</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1122
#, no-c-format
msgid "Print log of item"
msgstr "Natisnite dnevnik predmeta"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1123
#, no-c-format
msgid "-r startrevision:endrevision -l limit_display"
msgstr "-r startrevision:endrevision -l limit_display"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1126
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>cat</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>mačka</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1127
#, no-c-format
msgid "Display content of item"
msgstr "Prikaz vsebine predmeta"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1128 index.docbook:1153 index.docbook:1163
#, no-c-format
msgid "-r revision"
msgstr "-r revizija"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1131
#, no-c-format
msgid "copy (or cp)"
msgstr "kopija (ali cp)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Copy item inside working copy or repository. If target isn't given, &kdesvn; "
"will prompt."
msgstr ""
"Kopirajte element znotraj delovne kopije ali repozitorija. Če cilj ni podan, "
"&kdesvn; bo pozval."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1136
#, no-c-format
msgid "move (or mv, rename)"
msgstr "premakni (ali mv, preimenuj)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1137
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Move/Rename item inside working copy or repository. If target isn't given, "
"&kdesvn; will prompt."
msgstr ""
"Premakni/preimenuj element znotraj delovne kopije ali repozitorija. Če cilj "
"ni podan, bo &kdesvn; pozval."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1141 index.docbook:1255
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>get</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>dobi</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1142
#, no-c-format
msgid "Get content of item and save it"
msgstr "Pridobite vsebino predmeta in ga shranite"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1143
#, no-c-format
msgid "-r revision -o &lt;outputfile&gt; (output is required!)"
msgstr "--r revision -o &lt;outputfile&gt; (izhod je obvezen!)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1146
#, no-c-format
msgid "blame (or annotate)"
msgstr "očitati (ali označiti)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1147
#, no-c-format
msgid "annotate file"
msgstr "datoteka z opombami"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1148
#, no-c-format
msgid "-r startrevision:endrevision"
msgstr "-r startrevision:endrevision"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1151
#, no-c-format
msgid "update"
msgstr "posodobitev"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1152
#, no-c-format
msgid "Update item in working copy"
msgstr "Posodobi element v delovni kopiji"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1156
#, no-c-format
msgid "diff"
msgstr "diff"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1157
#, no-c-format
msgid "Diff two revisions of item or diff two items at specific revision"
msgstr ""
"Razlikuje dve reviziji postavke ali razlikuje dve postavki pri določeni "
"reviziji"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1158 index.docbook:1208
#, no-c-format
msgid "-r startrev:endrev"
msgstr "-r startrev:endrev"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1161
#, no-c-format
msgid "info"
msgstr "info"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1162
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detailed information about the item"
msgstr "Podrobne informacije o predmetu"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1166
#, no-c-format
msgid "checkout (or co)"
msgstr "checkout (ali co)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1167
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Checkout repository-path into a new working copy path. Target path and "
"source revision will be asked for."
msgstr ""
"Prevzemi pot repozitorija v novo pot delovne kopije. Zahtevana bo revizija "
"ciljne poti in vira."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1171
#, no-c-format
msgid "checkoutto (or coto)"
msgstr "checkoutto (ali coto)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Checkout repository-path into a new working copy path. The difference of the "
"source path and source revision will be asked for."
msgstr ""
"Prevzemi pot repozitorija v novo pot delovne kopije. Zahtevana bo razlika "
"med izvorno potjo in izvorno revizijo."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1176
#, no-c-format
msgid "export"
msgstr "export"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1177
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Export repository- or working copy-path into directory. Target path and "
"source revision will be asked for."
msgstr ""
"Izvozi pot repozitorija ali delovne kopije v imenik. Zahtevana bo revizija "
"ciljne poti in vira."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1181
#, no-c-format
msgid "exportto"
msgstr "exportto"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1182
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Export repository- or working copy-path into directory. Source path and "
"source revision will be asked for."
msgstr ""
"Izvozi pot repozitorija ali delovne kopije v imenik. Zahtevana bo izvorna "
"pot in revizija vira."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1186
#, no-c-format
msgid "delete (del, remove, rm)"
msgstr "izbriši (del, odstrani, rm)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1187
#, no-c-format
msgid "delete url(s) from repository or working copy."
msgstr "izbrišite url(-e) iz repozitorija ali delovne kopije"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1191
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>add</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>dodaj</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"add &URL; to working copy. &URL; must belong to a working copy (its not an "
"import!)"
msgstr ""
"dodaj &URL; v delovno kopijo. &URL; mora pripadati delovni kopiji (to ni "
"uvoz!)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1196
#, no-c-format
msgid "revert (or undo)"
msgstr "povrni (ali razveljavi)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1197
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"undone current changes to working copy. May only used on working copy urls!"
msgstr ""
"razveljavljene trenutne spremembe delovne kopije. Lahko se uporablja samo na "
"URL-jih delovne kopije!"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1201
#, no-c-format
msgid "checknew (or addnew)"
msgstr "preveri novo (ali dodaj novo)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1202
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"check in given &URL; for new, unversioned items and add them to working copy "
"if wanted."
msgstr ""
"preveri dani &URL; za nove postavke brez različic in jih po želji dodajte v "
"delovno kopijo."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1206
#, no-c-format
msgid "tree"
msgstr "drevo"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1207
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"displays revision tree of item (only first argument), if &URL; with <quote>?"
"rev=<replaceable>xxx</replaceable></quote> given, this revision is the peg-"
"revision."
msgstr ""
"prikaže revizijsko drevo postavke (samo prvi argument), če &URL; če je "
"podano <quote>?rev=<replaceable>xxx</replaceable></quote>, je ta revizija "
"peg-revizija."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1211
#, no-c-format
msgid "lock"
msgstr "zaklepanje"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1212
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"lock url(s), if <option>-f</option> is given then existing locks are broken."
msgstr ""
"zakleni url(-e), če je podana <option>-f</option>, so obstoječe ključavnice "
"pokvarjene."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1213 index.docbook:1219
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>-f</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>-f</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1216
#, no-c-format
msgid "unlock"
msgstr "unlock"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1217
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"unlock url(s), if <option>-f</option> is given then not owned locks are "
"broken or non existing locks are ignored."
msgstr ""
"odkleni url(-e), če je podana <option>-f</option>, se zaklepanje, ki ni v "
"lasti, zlomljen ali pa se zaklepanje, ki ne obstaja, prezre."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1222
#, no-c-format
msgid "help"
msgstr "pomoč"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1223
#, no-c-format
msgid "displays this page"
msgstr "prikaže to stran"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1232
#, no-c-format
msgid "Parameter for subversion commands"
msgstr "Parameter za subversion ukaze"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1236
#, no-c-format
msgid "Parameter"
msgstr "Parameter"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1237
#, no-c-format
msgid "Possible values"
msgstr "Možne vrednosti"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1238
#, no-c-format
msgid "allowed for"
msgstr "dovoljeno za"

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1243
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-r</option>"
msgstr "<option>-r</option>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1244
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<replaceable>revision</replaceable> or <replaceable>startrev:endrev</"
"replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<replaceable>revision</replaceable> ali <replaceable>startrev:endrev</"
"replaceable>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1245 index.docbook:1250
#, no-c-format
msgid "all except commit"
msgstr "vse razen commit"

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1248
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-R</option>"
msgstr "<option>-R</option>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1249 index.docbook:1264
#, no-c-format
msgid "(none)"
msgstr "(brez)"

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1253
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-o</option>"
msgstr "<option>-o</option>"

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:1254
#, no-c-format
msgid "filename"
msgstr "Ime datoteke"

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1258
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-l</option>"
msgstr "<option>-l</option>"

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:1259
#, no-c-format
msgid "number"
msgstr "število"

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1263
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-f</option>"
msgstr "<option>-f</option>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1265
#, no-c-format
msgid "(un-)lock"
msgstr "(un-)lock"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1274
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <quote>log</quote> command"
msgstr "Ukaz <quote>log</quote>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1275
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Log command displays a dialog containing the log of the given &URL;. With "
"subversion 1.2 or above it accepts a limit, &ie; how many entries it has to "
"display."
msgstr ""
"Ukaz dnevnika prikaže pogovorno okno, ki vsebuje dnevnik danega &URL;. S "
"subversion 1.2 ali novejšo sprejme omejitev, &ie;. koliko vnosov mora "
"prikazati."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1278
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Inside that dialog you may select log entries and get the differences "
"between them."
msgstr ""
"Znotraj tega pogovornega okna lahko izberete vnose v dnevnik in si ogledate "
"razlike med njimi."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1281
#, no-c-format
msgid "Display the last 20 commit logs"
msgstr "Prikaži zadnjih 20 dnevnikov objave"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1282
#, no-c-format
msgid "kdesvn exec log -l 20 -r HEAD&#058;1 myfile.c"
msgstr "kdesvn exec log -l 20 -r HEAD&#058;1 myfile.c"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1283
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Beware of order of revision: You want go from HEAD to START for the LAST "
"one. So you must give revision HEAD as starting point, otherwise you would "
"get the first 20 entries."
msgstr ""
"Pazite na vrstni red revizije: želite iti od GLAVE do ZAČETKA za ZADNJI. "
"Zato morate dati revizijo HEAD kot izhodišče, sicer bi dobili prvih 20 "
"vnosov."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1289
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <quote>diff</quote> command"
msgstr "Ukaz <quote>diff</quote>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1290
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You get differences between revisions of an item or between two items inside "
"same working copy or repository. When diff'ing revisions of an item, "
"revisions may be given as <option>-r <replaceable>STARTREV</replaceable>:"
"<replaceable>ENDREV</replaceable></option>. When diffing an item inside a "
"working copy without any revisions it prints the diff against repository."
msgstr ""
"Dobite razlike med revizijami postavke ali med dvema postavkama znotraj iste "
"delovne kopije ali repozitorija. Ko razlikujete revizije postavke, so lahko "
"revizije podane kot <option>-r <replaceable>STARTREV</replaceable>:"
"<replaceable>ENDREV</replaceable></option>. Pri razlikovanju postavke "
"znotraj delovne kopije brez kakršnih koli revizij natisne razliko glede na "
"repozitorij."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1293
#, no-c-format
msgid "Print difference against repository, &ie; local changes"
msgstr "Natisni razliko glede na repozitorij, &ie; lokalne spremembe"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1294
#, no-c-format
msgid "kdesvn exec diff myfile.c"
msgstr "kdesvn exec diff myfile.c"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1297
#, no-c-format
msgid "Print difference between revisions"
msgstr "Natisni razliko med revizijami"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1298
#, no-c-format
msgid "kdesvn exec diff -r 21:20 myfile.c"
msgstr "kdesvn exec diff -r 21:20 myfile.c"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1301
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When diffing two items revisions may be appended to &URL; of items. &eg;:"
msgstr "Pri razlikovanju med dvema elementoma se lahko &URL; predmetov. &eg;:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1303
#, no-c-format
msgid "http://server/path/item?rev=HEAD"
msgstr "http://server/path/item?rev=HEAD"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1305
#, no-c-format
msgid "Diffing two tagged versions"
msgstr "Razlikovanje med dvema označenima različicama"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1306
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"kdesvn exec diff http://www.alwins-world.de/repos/kdesvn/tags/rel_0_6_2 "
"http://www.alwins-world.de/repos/kdesvn/tags/rel_0_6_3"
msgstr ""
"kdesvn exec diff http://www.alwins-world.de/repos/kdesvn/tags/rel_0_6_2 "
"http://www.alwins-world.de/repos/kdesvn/tags/rel_0_6_3"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1314
#, no-c-format
msgid "Settings"
msgstr "Nastavitve"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1315
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Settings can be changed from the setup dialog. They are separated into some "
"subdialogs."
msgstr ""
"Nastavitve lahko spremenite v pogovornem oknu za nastavitev. Ločene so v "
"nekaj podoken."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1319
#, no-c-format
msgid "General"
msgstr "Splošno"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1325
#, no-c-format
msgid "Size of listviewicons"
msgstr "Velikost ikon za ogled seznama"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1326
#, no-c-format
msgid "How big (square) the icons in main list view should be"
msgstr "Kako velike (kvadratne) naj bodo ikone v pogledu glavnega seznama"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1329
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show file info"
msgstr "Pokaži informacije o datoteki"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1330
#, no-c-format
msgid "If a small tooltip should appear when moving mouse over an item"
msgstr "Če se ob premikanju miške nad element prikaže majhen namig"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1333
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mark item status with icon overlay"
msgstr "Označi status elementa s prekrivno ikono"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1334
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When an item isn't in normal subversion state it may get an overlay. (See "
"<xref linkend=\"overlay-meaning\"/>)"
msgstr ""
"Ko postavka ni v normalnem stanju subversion, lahko dobi prekrivanje. "
"(Glejte <xref linkend=\"overlay-meaning\"/>)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1337
#, no-c-format
msgid "Items sorting order is case sensitive"
msgstr ""
"Vrstni red razvrščanja elementov razlikuje med velikimi in malimi črkami"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1338
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the sort order in main window is case sensitive or not, &ie; if <quote>a</"
"quote> not equal to <quote>A</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Če je vrstni red v glavnem oknu občutljiv na velike in male črke ali ne, "
"&ie;. če <quote>a</quote> ni enak <quote>A</quote>."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1341
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>Display ignored files</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>Prikaži prezrte datoteke</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1342
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>Show items marked in subversion for ignore or not.</entry>"
msgstr ""
"<entry>Prikaži elemente, ki so v programu subversion označeni za prezrtje "
"ali ne.</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1345
#, no-c-format
msgid "Maximum log messages in history"
msgstr "Največje število dnevniških sporočil v zgodovini"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1346
#, no-c-format
msgid "How many log messages &kdesvn; should remember."
msgstr "Koliko dnevniških sporočil &kdesvn; bi se moral spomniti."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1349
#, no-c-format
msgid "Display colored annotate"
msgstr "Prikaži barvno opombo"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1350
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use colors defined in the settings dialog for annotations."
msgstr "Za opombe uporabite barve, določene v pogovornem oknu z nastavitvami."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1353
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use navigation panel"
msgstr "Uporabite navigacijsko ploščo"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1354
#, no-c-format
msgid "Toggle the display of the repository tree view."
msgstr "Preklopi prikaz drevesnega pogleda repozitorija."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1364
#, no-c-format
msgid "Subversion and timed jobs settings"
msgstr "Subversion in nastavitve časovno določenih opravil"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1367
#, no-c-format
msgid "Subversion"
msgstr "Subversion"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1373
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start check for updates when open a working copy"
msgstr "Zaženite preverjanje posodobitev, ko odprete delovno kopijo"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1374
#, no-c-format
msgid "When open a working copy start a check for updates in background"
msgstr "Ko odprete delovno kopijo, zaženite preverjanje posodobitev v ozadju"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1377
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start fill log cache on open"
msgstr "Začni izpolnjevati predpomnilnik dnevnika ob odprtju"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1378
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If set &kdesvn; start (re-)filling the log cache when open a repository or "
"working copy if repository &URL; is not assigned local (<filename class="
"\"directory\">file://</filename>)"
msgstr ""
"Če je nastavljen &kdesvn; začnite (ponovno) polniti predpomnilnik dnevnika, "
"ko odprete repozitorij ali delovno kopijo, če repozitorij &URL; ni dodeljeno "
"lokalno (<filename class=\"directory\">file://</filename>)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1381
#, no-c-format
msgid "Check if items has <quote>svn:needs-lock</quote> set"
msgstr "Preverite, ali ima element nastavljen <quote>svn:need-lock</quote>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1382
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check on working copies if an item has this property set and if yes, "
"displays a special overlayed icon. Setting this may let listings get real "
"slow."
msgstr ""
"V delovnih kopijah preverite, ali ima element nastavljeno to lastnost, in če "
"je, prikaže posebno prekrivno ikono. Če to nastavite, lahko povzročite, da "
"bodo seznami zelo počasni."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1385
#, no-c-format
msgid "Get file details while remote listing"
msgstr "Pridobite podrobnosti o datoteki med oddaljenim seznamom"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When checked, &kdesvn; get more detailed info about file items when making a "
"listing to remote repositories. So you may see remote locks in overview. Be "
"careful: This may let listings REAL slow!"
msgstr ""
"Ko je označeno, &kdesvn; pridobi podrobnejše informacije o elementih "
"datotek, ko ustvarjate seznam v oddaljenih repozitorijih. Tako boste morda "
"videli oddaljene ključavnice v pregledu. Bodite previdni: zaradi tega se "
"bodo seznami RESNIČNO upočasnili!"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1390
#, no-c-format
msgid "Gain item info recursive"
msgstr "Rekurzivno pridobivanje informacij"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1391
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When activated, <command>info</command> on folders will gain information "
"about all items below, may be real slow."
msgstr ""
"Ko je aktiviran, bo <command>info</command> v mapah pridobil informacije o "
"vseh spodnjih elementih, kar je lahko zelo počasno."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1395
#, no-c-format
msgid "Store passwords for remote connections"
msgstr "Shranite gesla za oddaljene povezave"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1396
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Storing passwords is often a security problem. Subversion stores its "
"passwords into a flat file, &ie; passwords in the plain text! So be careful "
"setting this flag and see next entry, too. This item only says if saving "
"passwords is the default, you may change it for specific realms inside login "
"dialog."
msgstr ""
"Shranjevanje gesel je pogosto varnostna težava. Subversion shrani svoja "
"gesla v ravno datoteko, &ie; gesla v navadnem besedilu! Zato bodite previdni "
"pri nastavitvi te zastavice in si oglejte tudi naslednji vnos. Ta element "
"pravi le, če je shranjevanje gesel privzeto, ga lahko spremenite za določena "
"področja znotraj prijavnega pogovornega okna."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1400
#, no-c-format
msgid "Store passwords into KDE Wallet"
msgstr "Shrani gesla v listnico KDE Wallet"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1401
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When saving passwords, the plain text file from subversion is a security "
"hole. &kdesvn; is able saving them into encrypted &kde; wallet instead there "
"(starting with version 0.12.0) and use them. On other hand other subversion "
"clients aren't able reading them so you must enter them if using tools like "
"<application>svn</application> command line tool or <application>rapidsvn</"
"application>, too. As long as subversion does not encrypt password storage "
"you should think twice about it."
msgstr ""
"Pri shranjevanju gesel je datoteka z navadnim besedilom iz subversion "
"varnostna luknja. &kdesvn; jih lahko shrani v šifrirano &kde; listnico "
"(začenši z različico 0.12.0) in jih uporabite. Po drugi strani pa jih drugi "
"odjemalci programa subversion ne morejo prebrati, zato jih morate vnesti "
"tudi, če uporabljate orodja, kot je orodje ukazne vrstice <application>svn</"
"application> ali <application>rapidsvn</application>. Dokler subversion ne "
"šifrira shranjevanja gesel, morate o tem dvakrat premisliti."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1405
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use internal password cache"
msgstr "Uporabi notranji predpomnilnik gesel"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1406
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a password is not stored persistent &kdesvn; may hold it until &kdesvn; "
"ends, so you may not need to enter it again for each operation. This cache "
"is never persistent, &ie; it will not be saved anywhere."
msgstr ""
"Ko geslo ni shranjeno, obstojni &kdesvn; ga lahko zadrži, dokler &kdesvn; "
"konča, zato vam ga morda ne bo treba znova vnesti za vsako operacijo. Ta "
"predpomnilnik ni nikoli obstojen, &ie; ne bo nikjer shranjeno."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1410
#, no-c-format
msgid "Log follows node changes"
msgstr "Dnevnik sledi spremembam vozlišča"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1411
#, no-c-format
msgid "If checked log follows copy operations."
msgstr "Če je označeno, dnevnik sledi operacijam kopiranja."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1415
#, no-c-format
msgid "Log always reads list of changed files"
msgstr "Dnevnik vedno prebere seznam spremenjenih datotek"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1416
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The log command may read list of changed files in commit. This is useful and "
"in most cases it cost not real more traffic."
msgstr ""
"Ukaz log lahko prebere seznam spremenjenih datotek v potrditvi. To je "
"uporabno in v večini primerov ne stane resnično več prometa."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1420
#, no-c-format
msgid "Review items before commit"
msgstr "Preglej elemente pred potrjevanjem"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1421
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When doing a commit &kdesvn; may make a check what to do. For example, if "
"unversioned items are below which may be added, list items changed and "
"current operation will commit. This cost a depending on tree more or less "
"time."
msgstr ""
"Ko izvajate potrjevanje &kdesvn; lahko preveri, kaj storiti. Na primer, če "
"so spodaj elementi brez različic, ki jih je mogoče dodati, se spremenijo "
"elementi seznama in trenutna operacija se potrdi. To stane odvisno od "
"drevesa več ali manj časa."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1425
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hide new items in commit box"
msgstr "Skrij nove elemente v polju za objavo"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1426
#, no-c-format
msgid "Should unversioned items displayed in commit dialog or not."
msgstr ""
"Ali naj bodo elementi brez različic prikazani v pogovornem oknu za objavo "
"ali ne."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1430
#, no-c-format
msgid "Update modifies instead of conflicts"
msgstr "Posodobitev spreminja namesto konfliktov"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1431
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If set, a local addition at the same path as an incoming addition of the "
"same node kind results in a normal node with a possible local modification, "
"instead of a tree conflict."
msgstr ""
"Če je nastavljeno, lokalni dodatek na isti poti kot dohodni dodatek iste "
"vrste vozlišča povzroči običajno vozlišče z možno lokalno spremembo namesto "
"konflikta drevesa."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1437
#, no-c-format
msgid "Update makes missing parents"
msgstr "Posodobitev naredi manjkajoče starše"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1438
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If set, create any non-existent parent directories also by checking them out "
"at depth=empty"
msgstr ""
"Če je nastavljeno, ustvarite vse neobstoječe nadrejene imenike tudi tako, da "
"jih preverite na depth=empty"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1448
#, no-c-format
msgid "Timed jobs"
msgstr "Časovno določena delovna mesta"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1452
#, no-c-format
msgid "Check modified items every N seconds"
msgstr "Preverite spremenjene elemente vsakih N sekund"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1452
#, no-c-format
msgid "Check for updated items every N seconds"
msgstr "Preverite posodobljene elemente vsakih N sekund"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:1453
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If set check for updates or modified items in working copy when network is "
"enabled on regular base"
msgstr ""
"Če je nastavljeno, preveri posodobitve ali spremenjene elemente v delovni "
"kopiji, ko je omrežje redno omogočeno"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1462
#, no-c-format
msgid "Diff &amp; Merge"
msgstr "Diff &amp; Spoji"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1467
#, no-c-format
msgid "Diff ignores content type"
msgstr "Diff ignorira vrsto vsebine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1468
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only interesting when diff are made with subversion itself. When set, than "
"subversion diff ignores the content type of entries. Otherwise it will not "
"output diffs from binaries."
msgstr ""
"Zanimivo samo, če so razlike narejene s programom subversion. Ko je "
"nastavljen, subversion diff prezre tip vsebine vnosov. V nasprotnem primeru "
"ne bo izpisal razlik iz binarnih datotek."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1475
#, no-c-format
msgid "Diff in revision tree is recursive"
msgstr "Diff v revizijskem drevesu je rekurziven"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1476
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When set, diffs made from within revision tree view are made recursive like "
"in all other cases, too. Otherwise only changes belonging to that folder "
"items are shown. How that is made depends on how you let diffs generate "
"(from subversion itself or from external viewers)."
msgstr ""
"Ko so nastavljene, so razlike, narejene znotraj drevesnega pogleda revizij, "
"rekurzivne kot v vseh drugih primerih. V nasprotnem primeru so prikazane "
"samo spremembe, ki pripadajo elementom te mape. Kako je to narejeno, je "
"odvisno od tega, kako dovolite ustvarjanje razlik (iz samega programa  "
"subversion ali iz zunanjih ogledovalnikov)."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1481
#, no-c-format
msgid "Diff ignores white space changes"
msgstr "Diff ignorira spremembe belega prostora"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1483
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Ignore changes in the amount of white space (option <option>-b</option> to "
"<application>diff</application>)"
msgstr ""
"Ignoriraj spremembe v količini belega prostora (možnost <option>-b</option> "
"do <application>diff</application>)"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1489
#, no-c-format
msgid "Diff ignores all white spaces"
msgstr "Diff ignorira vse bele prostore"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1491
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignore all white space (option <option>-w</option> to diff)"
msgstr "Prezri vse bele prostore (možnost <option>-w</option> za diff)"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1495 index.docbook:1552
#, no-c-format
msgid "Prefer external merge program"
msgstr "Prednost dajte zunanjemu programu združevanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1497
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set if merge with external program is preferred and not Subversion's merge"
msgstr ""
"Nastavite, ali je prednostno spajanje z zunanjim programom in ne spajanje "
"Subversion"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1501
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use Git diff format"
msgstr "Uporabite format Git diff"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1507
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show copies as add"
msgstr "Prikaži kopije kot dodatek"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1516
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use external diff display"
msgstr "Uporabi zunanji diff display"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1517
#, no-c-format
msgid "Selects an external application to display diffs. Default is &kompare;."
msgstr "Izbere zunanjo aplikacijo za prikaz razlik. Privzeto je &kompare;."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1522
#, no-c-format
msgid "External diff display"
msgstr "Zunanji prikaz dif"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1523
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines what &kdesvn; is using for external display of differences and how "
"it will be called. There are three ways:"
msgstr ""
"Določa, kaj &kdesvn; uporablja za zunanji prikaz razlik in kako se bo "
"imenoval. Obstajajo trije načini:"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1529
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;program&gt; &lt;parameter&gt;"
msgstr "&lt;program&gt; &lt;parameter&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1530
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The difference will generated with subversion and put direct into standard "
"input of the external program (&ie;, no temporary files needed)"
msgstr ""
"Razlika bo ustvarjena s subversion in vnesena neposredno v standardni vnos "
"zunanjega programa (&ie; začasne datoteke niso potrebne)"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1536
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;program&gt; &lt;parameter&gt; %f"
msgstr "&lt;program&gt; &lt;parameter&gt; %f"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1537
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The difference will be generated with subversion, saved into a temporary "
"file and the parameter <option>%f</option> will be replaced with that file "
"name. This may be used, for instance, with a simple call to "
"<application>less</application> or text viewer."
msgstr ""
"Razlika bo ustvarjena s subversion, shranjena v začasno datoteko in "
"parameter <option>%f</option> bo nadomeščen s tem imenom datoteke. To lahko "
"uporabite na primer s preprostim klicem <application>less</application> ali "
"pregledovalnika besedila."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1544
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;program&gt; &lt;parameter&gt; %1 %2"
msgstr "&lt;program&gt; &lt;parameter&gt; %1 %2"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1545
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdesvn; let the external program make the difference. %1 and %2 will be "
"replaced with required values (file names or folder names). &kdesvn; stores "
"content to compare in a temporary environment (when folders does an "
"<quote>export</quote>, when single file, does a <quote>cat</quote>) when "
"needed and cleans up after closing external program or closing itself."
msgstr ""
"&kdesvn; naj zunanji program naredi razliko. %1 in %2 bosta zamenjana z "
"zahtevanimi vrednostmi (imeni datotek ali map). &kdesvn; shrani vsebino za "
"primerjavo v začasnem okolju (ko mape izvede <quote>izvoz</quote>, ko "
"posamezno datoteko, naredi <quote>cat</quote>), ko je to potrebno, in "
"počisti, ko zapre zunanji program ali se sam zapre."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1553
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select if in merge dialog <guilabel>Use external merge</guilabel> should be "
"checked or not as default."
msgstr ""
"Izberite, ali naj bo v pogovornem oknu za spajanje <guilabel>Uporabi zunanje "
"spajanje</guilabel> označeno ali ne kot privzeto."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1559
#, no-c-format
msgid "External merge program"
msgstr "Zunanji program za spajanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1560
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Setup the program and options for using when subversion's builtin merge "
"isn't wanted. The default is <command>kdiff3 %s1 %s2 %t</command>. The order "
"of substitution variables isn't important, and them may there more than "
"once, &eg; like <literal>kdiff3 -o %t %s1 %s2 %t</literal>. This stuff is "
"only tested with <application>meld</application> and &kdiff3;. Think about "
"that external programs mostly do not know anything about subversion "
"<command>ignore</command> parameter so them may show lot more than expected."
msgstr ""
"Nastavite program in možnosti za uporabo, ko vgrajeno spajanje subversion ni "
"zaželeno. Privzeta vrednost je <command>kdiff3 %s1 %s2 %t</command>. Vrstni "
"red nadomestnih spremenljivk ni pomemben in lahko so tam večkrat, &eg; kot "
"<literal>kdiff3 -o %t %s1 %s2 %t</literal>. Te stvari so testirane samo z "
"<application>meld</application> in &kdiff3;. Pomislite, da zunanji programi "
"večinoma ne vedo ničesar o parametru subversion <command>ignore</command>, "
"zato lahko pokažejo veliko več od pričakovanega."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1564
#, no-c-format
msgid "Variable substitutions for external merge program"
msgstr "Zamenjave spremenljivk za zunanji združevalni program"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1569
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>%s1</term>"
msgstr "<term>%s1</term>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1570
#, no-c-format
msgid "Substituted with source number one."
msgstr "Zamenjano z virom številka ena."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1576
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>%s2</term>"
msgstr "<term>%s2</term>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1577
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Substituted with source number two. If this is empty or this is equal to "
"source one and start and end revision is same, this variable will skipped. "
"So be careful setting up command lines like <command>xxdiff --title1 %s1 --"
"title2 %s2 %s1 %s2 %t</command>."
msgstr ""
"Zamenjano z virom številka dve. Če je to prazno ali je to enako izvirniku in "
"sta začetna in končna revizija enaki, bo ta spremenljivka preskočena. Zato "
"bodite previdni pri nastavljanju ukaznih vrstic, kot je <command>xxdiff --"
"title1 %s1 --title2 %s2 %s1 %s2 %t</command>."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1584 index.docbook:1625
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>%t</term>"
msgstr "<term>%t</term>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1585
#, no-c-format
msgid "Substituted with target."
msgstr "Zamenjano s ciljem."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1596
#, no-c-format
msgid "Conflict resolver program"
msgstr "Program za reševanje konfliktov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1597
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You may use an external program like &kdiff3; for resolving conflicts, the "
"default is <command>kdiff3 %o %m %n -o %t</command>."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite lahko zunanji program, kot je &kdiff3; privzeto je za reševanje "
"konfliktov <command>kdiff3 %o %m %n -o %t</command>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1602
#, no-c-format
msgid "Variable substitution for external conflict resolver"
msgstr "Zamenjava spremenljivke za zunanjega razreševalnika konfliktov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1603
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In parenthesis after each description is an example how subversion would "
"call the files. These options are designed for &kdiff3;, because at this "
"moment this is the only one application supporting all parameters required "
"for a good conflict resolving."
msgstr ""
"V oklepaju za vsakim opisom je primer, kako bi program subversion klical "
"datoteke. Te možnosti so zasnovane za &kdiff3;, ker je to trenutno edina "
"aplikacija, ki podpira vse parametre, potrebne za dobro reševanje konfliktov."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1607
#, no-c-format
msgid "%o or %l"
msgstr "%o ali %l"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1608
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Old (local, left) version. This means the lower revision number, &ie; the "
"start point of conflicted changes. (<filename>foo.cc.r2</filename>)"
msgstr ""
"Stara (lokalna, leva) različica. To pomeni nižjo številko revizije, &ie; "
"izhodišče konfliktnih sprememb. (<filename>foo.cc.r2</filename>)"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1613
#, no-c-format
msgid "%m or %w"
msgstr "%m ali %w"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1614
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Mine (working) version of file, &ie; what you had changed against old "
"version. (<filename>foo.cc.mine</filename>)"
msgstr ""
"Moja (delovna) različica datoteke, &ie; kaj ste spremenili glede na staro "
"različico. (<filename>foo.cc.mine</filename>)"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1619
#, no-c-format
msgid "%n or %r"
msgstr "%n ali %r"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1620
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"New (remote, right) version of file. For example, version someone other had "
"made. (<filename>foo.cc.r3</filename>)"
msgstr ""
"Nova (oddaljena, desna) različica datoteke. Na primer različica, ki jo je "
"naredil nekdo drug. (<filename>foo.cc.r3</filename>)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1626
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Target name, &eg; the origin name. For &kdiff3; (as an example) this would "
"be name after the <option>-o</option> parameter (= output file). "
"(<filename>foo.cc</filename>)"
msgstr ""
"Ime cilja, &eg; ime izvora. Za &kdiff3; (kot primer) bi bilo to ime za "
"parametrom <option>-o</option> (= izhodna datoteka). (<filename>foo.cc</"
"filename>)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1641
#, no-c-format
msgid "KIO / command line"
msgstr "KIO / ukazna vrstica"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1646
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show log after executing a command"
msgstr "Prikaži dnevnik po izvedbi ukaza"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1647
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Should a dialog open with the log of last subversion command when it was "
"executed via command line or &konqueror; action menu."
msgstr ""
"Če se odpre pogovorno okno z dnevnikom zadnjega ukaza subversion, ko je bil "
"ta izveden prek ukazne vrstice ali &konqueror; akcijski meni."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1653
#, no-c-format
msgid "Minimum log lines to show"
msgstr "Najmanjše število vrstic dnevnika za prikaz"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1654
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If <guilabel>Show log...</guilabel> is set, what is the minimum of lines "
"before such a dialog will shown. So you may set that such window will only "
"shown when interesting output was generated (commit log and so on)"
msgstr ""
"Če je <guilabel>Pokaži dnevnik ...</guilabel> nastavljen, kolikšno je "
"najmanjše število vrstic, preden se prikaže takšno pogovorno okno. Tako "
"lahko nastavite, da bo takšno okno prikazano le, ko je ustvarjen zanimiv "
"rezultat (dnevnik potrditve in tako naprej)"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1661
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do not display context menu in &konqueror;"
msgstr "Ne prikaži kontekstnega menija v &konqueror;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1662
#, no-c-format
msgid "If set, no action menu entry for &kdesvn; is made in &konqueror;."
msgstr ""
"Če je nastavljeno, ni vnosa menija dejanj za &kdesvn; je narejen v "
"&konqueror;."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1667
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do not display entries in toplevel action menu"
msgstr "Ne prikazuj vnosov v meniju dejanj na najvišji ravni"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1668
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If set, kdesvn will not show some extra actions inside <guimenuitem>Action</"
"guimenuitem> menu of &konqueror; or &dolphin;."
msgstr ""
"Če je nastavljen, kdesvn ne bo prikazal nekaterih dodatnih dejanj v meniju "
"<guimenuitem>Dejanje</guimenuitem> v &konqueror; ali &dolphin;."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1673
#, no-c-format
msgid "KIO operations use standard log message"
msgstr "Operacije KIO uporabljajo standardno dnevniško sporočilo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1674
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When making operations on a repository via the &kdesvn; KIO protocol from "
"within &konqueror; (&ie;, <quote>ksvn+...</quote> protocols) on large "
"operations like moving or copy folders &kdesvn; would ask for a log message "
"for each item. This is a behavior of &konqueror;. When this option is set, "
"the KIO implementation from &kdesvn; will not ask for a log message but set "
"a standard log message. This flag is not for the operations from &kdesvn; "
"action menu for &konqueror; but only copy/move/mkdir/delete made with "
"&konqueror; or other file managers on a KIO-url."
msgstr ""
"Pri izvajanju operacij na repozitoriju preko &kdesvn; KIO protokol znotraj "
"&konqueror; (&ie; <quote>ksvn+...</quote> protokoli) pri velikih operacijah, "
"kot je premikanje ali kopiranje map &kdesvn; zahteval sporočilo dnevnika za "
"vsak element. To je vedenje &konqueror;. Ko je ta možnost nastavljena, bo "
"implementacija KIO iz &kdesvn; ne bo zahteval sporočila dnevnika, temveč bo "
"nastavil standardno sporočilo dnevnika. Ta zastavica ni za operacije iz "
"&kdesvn; meni dejanj za &konqueror; ampak samo kopiranje/premaknitev/mkdir/"
"brisanje, narejeno s &konqueror; ali druge upravitelje datotek na KIO-url."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1682
#, no-c-format
msgid "Standard message"
msgstr "Standardno sporočilo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1683
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The message &kdesvn; KIO should set on operations from within &konqueror; "
"when the flag above is set. Default is <guilabel>Revision made with &kdesvn; "
"KIO</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Sporočilo &kdesvn; KIO bi moral nastaviti operacije znotraj &konqueror; ko "
"je zgornja zastavica nastavljena. Privzeto je <guilabel>Revizija narejena z "
"&kdesvn; KIO</guilabel>."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1689
#, no-c-format
msgid "KIO can overwrite"
msgstr "KIO lahko prepiše"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1690
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this flag is set, you will have a simple write support for existing "
"items. &eg; you can open files in your editor and save them direct without "
"checking out them before (&kdesvn; will do it in background)."
msgstr ""
"Če je ta zastavica nastavljena, boste imeli preprosto podporo za pisanje za "
"obstoječe elemente. &eg; datoteke lahko odprete v svojem urejevalniku in jih "
"neposredno shranite, ne da bi jih prej preverili (&kdesvn; bo to naredil v "
"ozadju)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1694
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use this only if you are sure what you are doing."
msgstr "Uporabite to le, če ste prepričani, kaj počnete."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1699
#, no-c-format
msgid "KIO shows progress messages"
msgstr "KIO prikazuje sporočila o napredku"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1700
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If set KIO shows in KDE's Plasma detailed information about current "
"operation. Error messages of KIO will always displayed and can "
"<emphasis>not</emphasis> be switched off."
msgstr ""
"Če je nastavljen, KIO prikaže v plazmi KDE podrobne informacije o trenutnem "
"delovanju. Sporočila o napakah KIO bodo vedno prikazana in jih <emphasis>ni</"
"emphasis> mogoče izklopiti."

